Package game

Class HighScoreTable

java.lang.Object
game.HighScoreTable
public class HighScoreTable extends Object
The HighScoreTable class manages the high scores for different levels in a game. It provides functionalities to add, retrieve, display, save, and load high scores.

    • addHighScore

      public void addHighScore(String level, int score)
      Adds or updates a high score for a specified level.
      Parameters:
      level - The level for which to set the high score.
      score - The score to set as the high score for the level.

    • getHighScore

      public int getHighScore(String level)
      Retrieves the high score for a specific level.
      Parameters:
      level - The level for which to get the high score.
      Returns:
      The high score for the specified level, or -1 if the level is not found.

    • displayHighScores

      public void displayHighScores()
      Displays all high scores stored in the table.

    • saveHighScoreTable

      public void saveHighScoreTable()
      Saves all high score data from the HashMap to an existing CSV file. The method writes each level's high score as a line in the CSV file.

    • loadHighScoreTable

      public void loadHighScoreTable()
      Loads the high score table from a CSV file. This method reads each line from the file and updates the high score HashMap.

    • getHighScores

      public static HashMap<String,Integer> getHighScores()
      Retrieves the high scores map containing scores for different levels. Each entry in the map consists of a level identifier as the key and its corresponding high score as the value.
      Returns:
      A HashMap<String, Integer> representing the high scores for different levels.

    • setHighScores

      public static void setHighScores(HashMap<String,Integer> highScores)
      Sets the high scores map for different levels. This method allows updating or replacing the existing high scores with a new map.
      Parameters:
      highScores - A HashMap<String, Integer> representing the new high scores to be set for different levels.
